  p.one-column-text.one-hand Tarantino announced the film in November 2013, stating it had originally started as a novel and sequel to Django Unchained. <strong><a href="#" class="red">After the script leaked in January 2014, he cancelled the film, but announced that he had changed</a></strong> his mind after directing a live reading of the script at the United Artists Theater in Los Angeles. Filming began on December 8, 2014, near Telluride, Colorado. The score, composed by Ennio Morricone, was his first complete Western score in 35.
