  p.one-column-text.one-hand Distributed by the Weinstein Company in the United States, <strong>The Hateful Eight</strong> was released on December 25, 2015. <strong><a href="#" class="red">In a roadshow release in 70mm film and had a wide digital release on December 30, 2015. It generally received positive reviews from critics</a></strong>. Some critics expressed unease at the abusive treatment of the Daisy Domergue character. For his work on the score, Morricone won the Golden Globe and the Academy Awars for best Original Score.
